## Writing Style (Skills, Prompts, CLAUDE.md, Memory)

Minimize tokens. Every word costs context.

- State the positive action, not the negative + alternative
- Drop filler: no "Please note that", "Make sure to", "You should always"
- One concept per bullet — split on "and" or ";"
- Don't restate what tools/context already provide
- When editing instructions, compress to this standard

# Knowledge Protocol

`~/.claude/memory/` is mandatory, not reference material.

## Before Acting (Lookup)

If the task matches a trigger, read the file before producing output:

| Trigger | Read |
|---------|------|
| Module/service design | `design-review.md` |
| Code or PR review | `code-review.md`, `pr-workflow.md` |
| Jira tickets | `jira-workflow.md` |
| Obsidian writes | `vault-conventions.md` |
